ce:section.ce:para:
Then, we performed the time-related decomposition process of 6 under different temperature. As shown in Fig. 8
                        , the color and intensity changes went fast with the temperature increasing from 230 °C to 270 °C that agreed with the composition rule. We also found that the variation curves of decomposition in Fig. 8 were not steady, which might be caused by the heat producer. So, we further heated 6 under 235 °C in a muffle roaster, in which a more steady curve was obtained that confirmed our point (Fig. 9
                        ).

